node.text:
Turtle cleaning! 🛀 🏝 Get your photos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting tourfervor.com 👉🏼 the link is in our bio: @tourfervor Why is this done?

A build up of algae and other waste can lead to skin disease so it’s important that we clean their shells often!
The brown and green on the turtles are a mix of algae and water scales. ***This turtle is being cleaned at a marine rescue centre / do not try this!! In the wild this is done by cleaner fish 🐟
Ogasawara-mura, Tokyo, Japan.
Video by @ogasawara_marine_centre and @unde_rwaterworld

Would you dare to hope this ride? 🤯 Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on tourfervor.com (link in my bio: @tourfervor

Desert dune ride via @caseycurrie 💨 Tag someone you wanna experience this with!

Sand Hollow State Park is a state park located in Utah, USA, featuring a 1,322-acre (535 ha) reservoir and an extensive off highway vehicle recreation area on Sand Mountain. The park is near the town of Hurricane.

The park was officially dedicated in April 2003 and surrounds the Sand Hollow Reservoir. Sand Hollow quickly became a popular site for camping, fishing, boating, and ATV riding on nearby sand dunes.

📽 @caseycurrie
📍 Sand Hollow State Park, Utah

node.text:
Switzerland's cliff walk is for thrill-seekers only via @michelphotographych 🇨🇭Get your photos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting tourfervor.com 👉🏼 the link is in our bio: @tourfervor

Would you be brave enough to walk through this high walkway suspended from a rocky mountainside, with peak & valley views, accessed by gondola?

About 300 meters long. It takes just 10-15 minutes to walk it in one direction, photo stops included. If you want to walk it both ways, count about half an hour for your visit.

The First Cliff Walk in Switzerland wraps around the mountains of Grindelwald and is a breathtaking experience for those brave enough to embark on the hike up the Bernese Alps. Most of the area is car free, First included. Grindelwald itself can be reached by car, but for nearly all other places you can travel by train and cable cars only.

Travel Tips: The easiest way to get to First Cliff Walk is by taking a 25-minutes gondola ride from Grindelwald to First. From there, it's just a short walk of 5 minutes to the Cliff Walk. You cannot drive up to First by car or by bus and hiking here from Grindelwald would take you several hours.

📽 @michelphotographych
📍Grindelwald, Switzerland
🎶 Ben Pellow - Roslyn
